DOCUMENT();       

loadMacros("PG.pl",
           "PGbasicmacros.pl",
           "PGchoicemacros.pl",
           "PGanswermacros.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl",
           "extraAnswerEvaluators.pl",
           "PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl"
           );
       
TEXT(beginproblem()); # standard preamble to each problem.


$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a1 = random(4000,6000,250);
$a2 = random(7000,9000,250);
$b1 = random(1.045,1.08,.005);
$k2 = random(0.067,0.083,.001);
$k1 = round(log($b1)/log(exp(1)) * 10000)/10000;
$b2 = "e^($k2)";
$b2_rd = round(exp($k2)*10000)/10000;

$ans = "ln($a2/$a1)/$diff";

BEGIN_TEXT
Question 38:
$BR $SPACE $BR
a) Let \( \ B=$a1($b1)^t \ \) give the balance of a bank account after $BITALIC t $EITALIC years. If the formula for $BITALIC B $EITALIC is written \( \ B=$a1 e^{kt} \ \), $SPACE estimate the value of $BITALIC k $EITALIC correct to four decimal places. 
$BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \ k \approx \) \{ ans_rule(30) \} (round to 4 decimal places)

$BR $SPACE $BR

b) The balance of a bank account after $BITALIC t $EITALIC years is given by the formula \( \ B= $a2 e^{$k2 t} \ \).  If the formula for $BITALIC B $EITALIC is written \( \ B= $a2 b^t \ \), $SPACE find $BITALIC b $EITALIC exactly, and give the value of $BITALIC b $EITALIC correct to four decimal places.
$BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \ b = \) \{ ans_rule(30) \} (EXACT) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \ b \approx \) \{ ans_rule(30) \} (round to 4 decimal places)

END_TEXT

ANS( num_cmp($k1,tol=>0.00007) );
ANS( num_cmp($b2,tol=>0.000000000001) );
ANS( num_cmp($b2_rd,tol=>0.00007) );

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$BR $SPACE $BR 
$BBOLD  SOLUTION $EBOLD
$BR 
a) We are given \( B = $a1 ($b1)^t \ \) and wish to express this equation in the form \( B = ae^{k t} \).  We know $BITALIC a $EITALIC = $a1, and now we set the two equivalent expression equal to each other and solve for $BITALIC k${EITALIC}:
$BR $SPACE $BR 
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ $a1 e^{kt} = $a1 ($b1)^t \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ e^{kt} = $b1^t \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ e^k = $b1 \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \ln{(e^k)} = \ln{($b1)} \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ k \ \ln{(e)} = \ln {($b1)} \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ k = \ln{($b1)} \approx $k1 \)
$BR $SPACE $BR
b) We are given \( B = $a2 e^{$k2 t} \ \) and wish to express this equation in the form \( B = ab^t \).  We know $BITALIC a $EITALIC = $a2, and now we set the two equivalent expression equal to each other and solve for $BITALIC b${EITALIC}:
$BR $SPACE $BR 
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ $a2 e^{$k2 t} = $a2 (b)^t \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ e^{$k2 t} = b^t \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ b = e^{$k2} \approx $b2_rd \)
$BR 
END_SOLUTION
ENDDOCUMENT(); 